==建筑 ==
[[File:Riverside_Church_from_Columbia_University.jpg|thumb]]校园看河滨教堂（左侧）]]
[[File:Riverside_Church_at_dusk.jpg|thumb]]
这座教堂的设计者是'''Allen, Pelton and Collens'''公司。洛克菲勒委托'''Henry C. Pelton'''和'''Charles Collens'''到[[西班牙|西班牙]]和[[法国|法国]]旅行，为这个工程寻找灵感。他们选用的原型是法国建于13世纪的哥特式教堂[[沙特尔大教堂|沙特尔大教堂]]，巨大的钟楼使得教堂其他部分显得矮小<!-- one of the towers at [[Notre-Dame_of_Laon|Laon]], but here with a base 100 feet square, and built on a steel frame 相当于22层的大厦(392 feet)<ref>[http://www.nyc-architecture.com/HAR/HAR009.htm 纽约建筑图片 - 河滨教堂]. Accessed July 31, 2006</ref>. Inlaid on the floor is a [[labyrinth|labyrinth]] similar to those at Chartres and elsewhere.这座教堂始建于1926年，由于一场木制脚手架引起的大火而使工程延期完成— with its first service at the main altar — 1930年10月5日。 -->

<!-- The exterior buttressing is purely decorative, for the structure is supported on its steel frame, and their weight would not be sufficient to counter the weight of the vault。''WPA Guide to New York City'' (1939)的作者 noted "Their smallness has the effect of making the building itself seem smaller than it is, so that its scale is scarcely impressive, even when seen at close range." -->

<!-- The south-facing main entrance, in the base of the tower, is based on the ''Porte Royale'' of Chartres, with the seated figure of Christ in[[tympanum_(architecture)|tympanum]], flanked by the symbols of the Evangelists. The figures sculpted in the concentric arches of the doorway represent leading personalities of 宗教和哲学, joined by great scientists. -->

钟楼里的钟琴是小洛克菲勒为纪念母亲<!-- Laura Spelman Rockefeller -->而捐赠，1925年起安置，后来又陆续增加钟的数目，最后拥有74个铜钟<!-- (当时世界最大的钟琴--see also [[Kirk_in_the_Hills|Kirk in the Hills]]) include the 20-ton bourdon, the largest cast and tuned  bell 现有。 

这座教堂从一开始就设计成一个综合的社会服务中心，拥有会议室、教室、日托中心、幼儿园、图书馆、礼堂和体育馆。 -->

==艺术品==
河滨教堂里悬挂着洛克菲勒购买的Heinrich Hofmann的3幅绘画作品：''基督在圣殿中'' (1871), ''基督与年轻的财主''(1889)，和''基督在客西马尼园'' (1890)。


